ive plants and animals may lead to massive social and or economic problems understanding the ecological and physical mechanisms behind these impacts can help society develop strategies to prevent detrimental changes as well as adapt to those changes that cannot be prevented 260 panama st stanford ca 94305 usa phone 650 462 1047 fax 650 462 5968 home about news people labs research calendars publications 2006 2008 carnegie institution
